<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1889-08-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1889-08-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="382" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d382">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Palmer</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Wharton</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1889-08-10"><hi rend="italic">August 10,
                            1889</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Letter addressed Blaine, the Department of State, and marked unofficial,
                        mailed August 3, should be read in connection with the note numbered 17 of
                        official note stating I had not put in Mora instruction.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Palmer.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>